# Cursor Pro — AU micro-SaaS / MVP rules

## Operator
- 1–2 person AU firm; Privacy Act + ACL; no PII in prompts; no regulated advice claims
- Cost ceiling A$5K/MVP; build 7–30 days; continuous testing max 5 cycles
- Y1 portfolio mindset: 50–55 bets, expect 1–2 winners (2.5% rule); 7-day cut rule on failing bets

## Model routing
- Architect (schema, security, multi-file plan): Opus 4.8 (default) | Fable 5 (hardest only, 5–10/mo) | GPT-5.6 Sol (UI / tool-calling)
- Daily coding / review: Sonnet 5 (default for ~90% of coding)
- Inline edits / boilerplate / docstrings: Haiku 4.5 or Luna via Cmd+K (~70% of edits)
- Multi-file scaffold: Composer 1 | Debug: BugBot | Unsure: Auto | Huge context: Max Mode
- NEVER use frontier (T1) for workhorse; NEVER use workhorse (T3) for architect

## Continuous testing loop
1. PLAN (T1) — ISC in 1–2 sentences + schema + file plan
2. BUILD (T2–T3) — Composer scaffold; Sonnet logic; Haiku Cmd+K polish
3. TEST — unit + manual smoke; capture failure modes
4. VERIFY (T2) — ISC met? if no, iterate (max 5 cycles)
5. FINALIZE — document outcome; update portfolio; cut if failing within 7 days

## Engineering
- Prefer TypeScript + Next.js App Router + Supabase + Stripe unless stack is specified
- Small focused diffs; ISC first; no drive-by refactors or unrelated cleanup
- AU English (colour, organise); currency A$; timezone-aware AU defaults where relevant
- Compliance / health / NDIS / legal-adjacent tools are assistive only — never present as regulated advice
- No secrets in repo; no real PII in fixtures or prompts

## Output
- Concise diffs; explain only when trade-offs matter
- Tests for money, auth, and data-integrity paths
- Include a short smoke checklist when shipping a feature
